2026-04-21 02:48:10 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['All switch indicator LEDs in control modules 1-8'] hypothesis_explanation="The absence of all control module indicator LEDs (physically missing) is consistent with the observed symptoms: none of the control module indicator LEDs turns on when the switches are closed, and the load lamp does not turn on, despite correct wiring and secure connections. Because the circuit through the load is series through all the control modules' switch LED-resistor branches, the physical absence of any (let alone all) of these indicator LEDs results in an open circuit and thus no current flow to the load. The PSU LED being on confirms power delivery as far as the power supply. Replacing the missing switch indicator LEDs would restore the series circuit required for the lamp to function."
